{
  "texts": [
    "For example, VineScout is a mobile robot that monitors moisture levels of soil and detects diseases in vineyards (Saiz-Rubio and Rovira-Más, 2020).",
    "These were achieved through a variety of devices including handheld devices and mobile robots (Saiz-Rubio and Rovira-Más, 2020; AgriFarming, 2022).",
    "The application of AI in agriculture offers numerous benefits, particularly in the development of efficient and intelligent irrigation systems.",
    "The use of Artificial Neural Network (ANN) models, such as those employed by Hinnell et al. (2010) and Arif et al. (2013) for soil moisture detection and intelligent irrigation, showcases the potential to ensure precise and optimal watering of crops.",
    "Additionally, the integration of Internet of Things (IoT) and ML, as demonstrated in the smart irrigation system by Tace et al. (2022), further enhances agricultural practices."
  ]
}